The following are major news items in leading Philippine
newspapers Wednesday. Manila Bulletin: -- The Supreme Court denied for
lack of merit Tuesday former President Joseph Estrada's motions that
sought to reconsider its March 2 decision upholding the legitimacy of
Gloria Macapagal- Arroyo's presidency and stripping him of his immunity
from suit. Manila Times: -- President Arroyo said Tuesday that she ill
push the development of Camp Abubakar and other camps previously
occupied by the Moro Islamic Liberation Front (MILF) so they can become
symbols of development, and not defiance under the new government.
Business World: -- The government is now less optimistic about
achieving the higher end of economic growth targets for the year
following the slowdown in the country's export sector, traditionally
the main source of growth in addition to provide investments.
